The paper discusses the ranking of web of data resources with associated textual data, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a query-biased algorithm that combines link analysis with dimensionality reduction, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses crowdsourcing for evaluation, which is a common technique in database (DB) research. Therefore, cs.DB is also a likely sub-category.
